Privacy Policy for Autoclick Chrome Extension
Effective Date: 26th Sept 2024
Company Name: DONEOLOGY LABS (OPC) PRIVATE LIMITED
CIN: U62013MH2024OPC416687
Jurisdiction: Mumbai, India

DONEOLOGY LABS (OPC) PRIVATE LIMITED ("we", "us", or "our") operates the Autoclick Chrome Extension (the "Extension"). This Privacy Policy outlines how we handle and protect user information, including data usage, storage, and permissions in relation to the Autoclick Chrome Extension.

1. Information Collection and Use
We want to assure you that Autoclick does not collect, store, or share any personal information. The extension operates locally on your device and does not transmit or retrieve any user data, personal or otherwise, from external servers.

2. Permissions Used
Autoclick uses the following permissions to function properly:

Storage: We use storage permissions to save your extension settings locally, such as your preferred hover delay and whether to open links in a new or the current tab. This information is stored solely on your device and is not shared with anyone.
activeTab: This permission is required to detect when you hover over a hyperlink and trigger the automatic opening of the page.
tabs: This permission is used to manage whether a new tab is opened or the current one is used, based on your preference.
Host Permissions: This is required to allow Autoclick to work on all websites you visit so it can open hyperlinks according to your set preferences.
3. Data Usage
Autoclick does not collect any personal information, browsing data, or user activity. Your settings are stored locally, and no information is shared with any third party.

4. Third-Party Data Sharing
DONEOLOGY LABS (OPC) PRIVATE LIMITED does not sell, share, or transfer any user data to third parties. Since the extension does not collect any data, there is no personal or non-personal information to be shared.

5. Data Security
Since Autoclick does not store any personal information or transmit any data, there is no risk of your information being exposed to unauthorized parties. Your preferences are stored locally on your device, and we do not have access to them.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or change this Privacy Policy at any time. Any significant changes will be communicated through updates to this article. Your continued use of the extension after any changes to the Privacy Policy will constitute your acknowledgment of the changes and consent to adhere to the updated policy.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
